              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Pacific/Midway"
            },
            "body": "How about allowing for AppLogAggregator to be pluggable? This would most likely be a pretty simple patch, there's only one place where AppLogAggregatorImpl is instantiated LogAggregationService.java\n\n{code}\n324     // New application\n325     final AppLogAggregator appLogAggregator =\n326         new AppLogAggregatorImpl(this.dispatcher, this.deletionService,\n327             getConfig(), appId, userUgi, dirsHandler,\n328             getRemoteNodeLogFileForApp(appId, user), logRetentionPolicy,\n329             appAcls);\n330     if (this.appLogAggregators.putIfAbsent(appId, appLogAggregator) != null) {\n331       throw new YarnRuntimeException(\"Duplicate initApp for \" + appId);\n332     }\n{code}",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ledion",
              "name": "ledion",
